Subject: Sectioned Periphery Association Fabric 098

Description: SOP-HG realization event for refining periphery into internal and external sections with primary and secondary document associations.

& [SectionedPeripheryAssociationFabric_098] is the realized periphery event
  + [event_status] is realized
  + [event_time] is 2026-06-25
  + [focus_subject] is Sectioned Periphery Association Fabric
  + [source_question] is how periphery should notice nearby elements, name strongly and weakly associated files, strengthen triangulation through primary documents, and distinguish internal file-surface periphery from external context/model periphery
  + [primary_realization] is periphery needs sections: internal periphery is the local file-surface web that can be browsed into focus, while external periphery is the general context and LLM model frame; stability must split into internal consistency stability and external model stability
  + [internal_periphery_section] is local specific file, subject, source, event, index, capture, and gate association
  + [external_periphery_section] is contextual frame, model lens, broad operating frame, and unspecified outside
  + [primary_document_association] is strong file association for triangulation
  + [secondary_document_association] is weak nearby association held available but not dominant
  + [wisdom_register] is the divided periphery makes browsing and triangulation cleaner because the system can know whether a signal comes from local file structure or external model framing
  + [caution_register] is primary and secondary association strength must not become proof, and external model stability must not replace local file-surface consistency
  + [balance_register] is stable because internal periphery, external periphery, primary files, secondary files, and the two stability layers remain distinct
  + [utility_horizon] is stronger job-node browser periphery panels, better subject lookup, primary-first triangulation, stability debugging, and safer model-lens comparison
  + [next_step] is keep Task_161 ready or later prototype a read-only internal periphery view model
  + [outside] is hidden model activations, proof by nearby files, exhaustive coverage, automatic promotion, stale path certainty, and broad model stability claims

  = must: keep internal and external periphery separate
  = must: weight primary documents more strongly than secondary documents without treating either as proof
  = should: surface primary and secondary document sets in browser and balance records

